f(x)=\frac{x^2}{\left(1-2x\right)^2}
x\to 2x
 |z|<1\implies \frac {1}{1-z} = \sum_{n=0}^\infty z^n;\\ \frac d{dx}\frac {1}{1-x} = \frac {1}{(1-x)^2}; |x|<1\implies \frac {1}{(1-x)^2} = \sum_{n=0}^\infty (n+1)x^n.\\ 
|x|<\frac 12\implies \frac {1}{(1-2x)^2} = \sum_{n=0}^\infty (n+1)2^nx^n\\ \implies \frac {x^2}{(1-2x)^2} = \sum_{n=0}^\infty (n+1)2^nx^{n+2}. 
x=1/2
(n+1)2^nx^{n+2}\nrightarrow 0
1/2
